@{
    Page.Title = "Custom editors";
    Layout = "~/Views/_Layout.cshtml";
}

<p>
    Web Essentials ships with a few extra editors.
</p>

<section>
    <h2>Robots.txt</h2>

    <article data-version="WE2012, WE2013">
        <h3>Syntax highlighting</h3>

        <p>Full colorization for comments and keywords in robots.txt.</p>
        <img src="/Images/custom-editors/robotstxt-colorizer.png" alt="robots.txt colorizer" />
    </article>

    <article data-version="WE2012, WE2013">
        <h3>Comment/uncomment</h3>

        <p>
            Two very useful commands is <mark>comment</mark> and <mark>uncomment</mark>.
            They are fully supported for WebVTT.
        </p>
    </article>

    <article data-version="WE2012, WE2013">
        <h3>Intellisense</h3>

        <p>Intellisense is also provided to make it easy to remember those different keywords.</p>
        <img src="/Images/custom-editors/robotstxt-intellisense.png" alt="robots.txt Intellisense" />
    </article>
</section>

<section>
    <h2>WebVTT - HTML5 subtitles</h2>

    <article data-version="WE2012, WE2013">
        <h3>Syntax highlighting</h3>

        <p>Full colorization for timestamps, custom markup and comments for .vtt files.</p>
        <img src="/Images/custom-editors/webvtt-colorizer.png" alt="WebVTT colorizer" />
    </article>

    <article data-version="WE2012, WE2013">
        <h3>Comment/uncomment</h3>

        <p>
            Two very useful commands is <mark>comment</mark> and <mark>uncomment</mark>.
            They are fully supported for WebVTT.
        </p>
    </article>
</section>